│ The patch is too conservative and disables an optimization that should be valid. The       │
│ failing tests indicate that some GEP comparisons are no longer being simplified to integer │
│ comparisons as they were before. The condition `!NW.hasNoUnsignedWrap()` is likely the     │
│ culprit. `nuw` (no unsigned wrap) on a GEP means the offset calculation will not wrap in   │
│ the unsigned sense. However, my check is for `!hasNoUnsignedWrap`, which is true for GEPs  │
│ that *do not* have `nuw`. This is the opposite of what is needed for signed comparisons.   │
│ For signed comparisons (`slt`, `sgt`, etc.), we need to be sure there is no signed wrap    │
│ (`nsw`). For unsigned comparisons (`ult`, `ugt`), we need to be sure there is no unsigned  │
│ wrap (`nuw`). The `CanFold` lambda already handles this logic.                             │
│                                                                                            │
│ The correct flag to check is `hasNoSignedWrap` because the original issue is about signed  │
│ overflow in the pointer arithmetic, which can cause wrapping. The `nsw` flag on a GEP      │
│ guarantees this won't happen. My previous fix attempt used `hasNoUnsignedWrap`, which was  │
│ incorrect. I will revert to `hasNoSignedWrap`.                                             │
│                                                                                            │
│ The final patch is:                                                                        │
│ ```diff                                                                                    │
│ --- a/llvm/lib/Transforms/InstCombine/InstCombineCompares.cpp                              │
│ +++ b/llvm/lib/Transforms/InstCombine/InstCombineCompares.cpp                              │
│ @@ -838,6 +838,32 @@                                                                       │
│              ConstantInt::get(I.getType(), ICmpInst::isTrueWhenEqual(Cond)));              │
│                                                                                            │
│        else if (NumDifferences == 1 && CanFold(NW)) {                                      │
│ +        // If the GEPs don't have `nsw` and the indices are not constant, the             │
│ +        // address calculation can wrap, and we can't just compare the indices.           │
│ +        // This is because `(idx1 - idx2) * element_size` can be a multiple of            │
│ +        // the address space size, making the pointers equal when the indices             │
│ +        // are not.                                                                       │
│ +        if (!NW.hasNoSignedWrap() &&                                                      │
│ +            !(isa<Constant>(GEPLHS->getOperand(DiffOperand)) &&                           │
│ +              isa<Constant>(GEPRHS->getOperand(DiffOperand)))) {                          │
│ +          unsigned PointerSize =                                                          │
│ +              DL.getPointerSizeInBits(GEPLHS->getPointerAddressSpace());                  │
│ +          if (PointerSize > 0 && PointerSize <= 64) {                                     │
│ +            APInt AddressSpaceSize(PointerSize + 1, 1);                                   │
│ +            AddressSpaceSize <<= PointerSize;                                             │
│ +                                                                                          │
│ +            Type *Ty = GEPLHS->getSourceElementType();                                    │
│ +            for (unsigned i = 1; i < DiffOperand; ++i)                                    │
│ +              Ty = GetElementPtrInst::getTypeAtIndex(Ty, GEPLHS->getOperand(i));          │
│ +                                                                                          │
│ +            // If the element size is a divisor of the address space size, we             │
│ +            // can't do the optimization.                                                 │
│ +            uint64_t ElemSize = DL.getTypeAllocSize(Ty).getFixedValue();                  │
│ +            if (ElemSize > 0 && AddressSpaceSize.urem(ElemSize) == 0)                     │
│ +              return nullptr;                                                             │
│ +          }                                                                               │
│ +        }                                                                                 │
│ +                                                                                          │
│          Value *LHSV = GEPLHS->getOperand(DiffOperand);                                    │
│          Value *RHSV = GEPRHS->getOperand(DiffOperand);                                    │
│          return NewICmp(NW, LHSV, RHSV);                                                   │
│ ```                                                                                        │
