│ The bug is an incorrect optimization of an equality comparison between two GEPs. The       │
│ optimization simplifies `icmp eq (gep P, I1), (gep P, I2)` to `icmp eq I1, I2`, which is   │
│ invalid if pointer arithmetic can wrap around the address space. This wrapping can make    │
│ the GEPs equal even if the indices `I1` and `I2` are different. This happens if `(I1 - I2) │
│ * element_size` is a non-zero multiple of the address space size.                          │
