│ guarantees that signed overflow, which causes this type of wrapping, will not occur. The   │
│ correct API for this is `hasNoSignedWrap()`.                                               │
│ 3.  The check only applies if the differing indices are not compile-time constants, as     │
│ constant-folding would handle those cases.                                                 │
│ 4.  If these conditions are met, it calculates the address space size and the element size │
│ at the differing GEP index. The address space size, `2^PointerSize`, is calculated         │
│ carefully as `APInt(PointerSize + 1, 1) << PointerSize` to avoid `APInt` assertion         │
│ failures.                                                                                  │
│ 5.  If the element size is a non-zero divisor of the address space size, wrapping is       │
│ possible. In this case, the optimization is conservatively disabled by returning           │
