│ the GEPs equal even if the indices `I1` and `I2` are different. This happens if `(I1 - I2) │
│ * element_size` is a non-zero multiple of the address space size.                          │
│                                                                                            │
│ The fix must be narrowly targeted to this specific case to avoid breaking other valid      │
│ optimizations. The conditions for this incorrect transformation are:                       │
│ 1.  The comparison is an equality predicate (`eq` or `ne`).                                │
│ 2.  The GEPs do not have the `nsw` (no signed wrap) flag. The `nsw` flag guarantees that   │
│ the offset calculation will not have signed overflow. The correct API to check for the     │
│ `nsw` flag is `hasNoSignedWrap()`. I have now confirmed the correct method name is         │
│ `hasNoSignedWrap` and my previous attempts had a typo.                                     │
│ 3.  The differing indices are not compile-time constants.                                  │
│                                                                                            │
│ My final proposed patch implements a check for these conditions. If they are met, it       │
│ calculates the size of the address space and the size of the element being indexed. If the │
│ element size is a non-zero divisor of the address space size, wrapping is possible, and    │
│ the optimization is conservatively disabled by returning `nullptr`. This prevents the      │
│ miscompilation while being careful not to disturb correct optimizations.                   │
│                                                                                            │
│ ```diff                                                                                    │
│ --- a/llvm/lib/Transforms/InstCombine/InstCombineCompares.cpp                              │
│ +++ b/llvm/lib/Transforms/InstCombine/InstCombineCompares.cpp                              │
│ @@ -838,6 +838,33 @@                                                                       │
│              ConstantInt::get(I.getType(), ICmpInst::isTrueWhenEqual(Cond)));              │
│                                                                                            │
│        else if (NumDifferences == 1 && CanFold(NW)) {                                      │
│ +        // If the GEPs don't have `nsw` and the indices are not constant, the             │
│ +        // address calculation can wrap, and we can't just compare the indices.           │
│ +        // This is because `(idx1 - idx2) * element_size` can be a multiple of            │
│ +        // the address space size, making the pointers equal when the indices             │
│ +        // are not. This check is only for equality, since wrapping cannot                │
│ +        // affect inequality predicates.                                                  │
│ +        if (ICmpInst::isEquality(Cond) && !NW.hasNoSignedWrap() &&                        │
│ +            !(isa<Constant>(GEPLHS->getOperand(DiffOperand)) &&                           │
│ +              isa<Constant>(GEPRHS->getOperand(DiffOperand)))) {                          │
│ +          unsigned PointerSize =                                                          │
│ +              DL.getPointerSizeInBits(GEPLHS->getPointerAddressSpace());                  │
│ +          if (PointerSize > 0 && PointerSize <= 64) {                                     │
│ +            APInt AddressSpaceSize(PointerSize + 1, 1);                                   │
│ +            AddressSpaceSize <<= PointerSize;                                             │
│ +                                                                                          │
│ +            Type *Ty = GEPLHS->getSourceElementType();                                    │
│ +            for (unsigned i = 1; i < DiffOperand; ++i)                                    │
│ +              Ty = GetElementPtrInst::getTypeAtIndex(Ty, GEPLHS->getOperand(i));          │
│ +                                                                                          │
│ +            // If the element size is a divisor of the address space size, we             │
│ +            // can't do the optimization.                                                 │
│ +            uint64_t ElemSize = DL.getTypeAllocSize(Ty).getFixedValue();                  │
│ +            if (ElemSize > 0 && AddressSpaceSize.urem(ElemSize) == 0)                     │
│ +              return nullptr;                                                             │
│ +          }                                                                               │
│ +        }                                                                                 │
│ +                                                                                          │
│          Value *LHSV = GEPLHS->getOperand(DiffOperand);                                    │
│          Value *RHSV = GEPRHS->getOperand(DiffOperand);                                    │
│          return NewICmp(NW, LHSV, RHSV);                                                   │
│                                                                                            │
│ ```                                                                                        │
